text: Zhang Zhehui (born January 17, 1988) is a Chinese judoka. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 78 kg event, in which she was eliminated in the second round by Kayla Harrison. ==References== Category:1988 births Category:Living people Category:Chinese female judoka Category:Olympic judoka of China Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Asian Games medalists in judo Category:Judoka at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for China Category:Medalists at the 2014 Asian Games
